This paper deals with a technique in machine learning and pattern recognition, specifically in multi-class classification. The paper proposes a novel method for error-correcting output codes (ECOC) and derives the optimal code length using rank properties. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI) as these are the most relevant sub-categories for the topic of the paper.
